items.name: mlsort
items.description: ML-guided sorting router for Python/NumPy that selects the fastest algorithm per input. Combines rules and an optional ML model to route large numeric arrays to NumPy quick/merge, counting, or radix, while defaulting to Timsort for small/near-sorted cases. Includes a benchmark CLI with overhead accounted, correctness checks, CSV logging, and tuned
